# ShopCursor Workshop Context

## Project Overview
This is a 2-day Cursor IDE training workshop with a sample e-commerce app called "ShopCursor."
The app sells developer-themed merchandise (hoodies, mugs, stickers, etc.).

## Intentional Code Smells
Some files contain INTENTIONAL code smells for refactoring exercises.
Files marked with `// WORKSHOP: Code smell` comments are meant to be improved during labs.
Do NOT auto-fix these unless explicitly asked in a lab exercise.

Key files with intentional smells:
- backend/src/main/java/com/shopcursor/service/CartService.java
- frontend/src/components/ProductList.tsx

## Lab Structure
- Labs have starter/ and solution/ directories
- starter/ contains the initial code participants work with
- solution/ contains the expected outcome — don't reference these during exercises

## When Generating Code
- Follow existing patterns in the ShopCursor codebase
- Use the developer-themed product data (Git Commit Hoodie, 404 Mug, etc.)
- Keep it simple — this is for learning, not production
- Add data-testid attributes for Playwright test selectors
